# Architecture Awareness

Before making ANY code changes, read the following files to understand impact:

1. `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — full dependency graph, state management, API contract
2. `docs/CJM.md` — customer journey maps, screen flows, pain points
3. `AUDIT.md` — known bugs and missing features

## Critical Dependency Chains

These files affect multiple features — changes require extra care:

- `packages/kodi_core/lib/api/nis_api.dart` → affects ALL features (auth, dashboard, practice, diagnostic, exam)
- `packages/kodi_core/lib/models/*` → affects ALL pages that display data
- `apps/kodi_web/lib/app/config.dart` → affects every API call (6 NisApiClient instances)
- `apps/kodi_web/lib/app/router.dart` → affects all navigation (7 routes)
- `apps/kodi_web/lib/shared/widgets/*` → affects PracticePage, DiagnosticPage, ExamPage

## Before Editing a File

1. Check the Impact Matrix in `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` to see what depends on this file
2. Check `docs/CJM.md` to understand which user journeys are affected
3. If changing a model or API method, trace all usages across the codebase
4. If changing a shared widget, test all 3 pages that use it (practice, diagnostic, exam)

## Known Architectural Issue

PracticePage, DiagnosticPage, and ExamPage create their own NisApiClient instances instead of using the shared RepositoryProvider. Keep this in mind when modifying auth or API logic.
